Being a vegetarian sometimes makes for a little anxiety when dining out. They mark little “v” marks on their menu to denote vegetarian items. I love mole! But as a vegetarian I’m often unable to eat it because of the chicken stock that is added to it. The waiter wasn’t able to answer my questions but the chef came out. The mole was vegetarian. No chicken stock or other animal flavorings. The chef told me they have a number of vegetarians that come in. I had enchiladas with the mole. Companion had the Chile Rellenos, also vegetarian. We both thoroughly enjoyed our meals. One warning though, while the beans are vegetarian, the rice is not. Almost every Mexican restaurant I go to uses a mix that contains chicken flavoring or they use chicken stock or both. Even when it’s listed under “vegetarian”. Notable exceptions were my two restaurants in upstate New York, El Loco Mexican Cafe (Albany)and Jose Malone’s Mexican Irish Restaurant (Troy). We made the rice from scratch with no animal products. One thing I didn’t check out until after eating was their patio. I didn’t see it until I was looking for the restroom. I did check it out. Reminded me of an outdoor restaurant I ate at in Tulum Mexico on New Years Eve (2019). Next time. I was on my way home a little later so I grabbed a couple of street tamales from a vendor on the nearby street corner.
